Meshy 3D Printing Workflow

Generate 3D-printable models from text or images using the Meshy API, then export directly to your slicer. This repo provides a complete, runnable pipeline from prompt to physical object.

Overview

This workflow covers four stages:

Generate — Create a 3D model via Text-to-3D or Image-to-3D API

Optimize — Remesh the model for print-ready topology and polycount

Export — Convert to .stl or .3mf (with optional multi-color support)

Slice & Print — Send to Bambu Studio, OrcaSlicer, Cura, or other supported slicers
